Document: CapsuleShape2D  
Path: godot/classes/class_capsuleshape2d.rst  
Summary: 2D physics shape used for collision detection with a capsule shape. Inherits from Shape2D < Resource < Object. Defines properties for radius, length, and collision layers.  

Inherits: Shape2D < Resource < Object  
Properties:  
- radius (float): Distance from center to capsule edge. Default: 0.5.  
- length (float): Length of the capsule along its local axis. Default: 1.0.  
- collision_layer (int): Bitmask defining which layers this shape collides with. Default: 0.  
- collision_mask (int): Bitmask defining which layers can collide with this shape. Default: 0.  

Methods:  
- set_radius(value: float) → void: Sets the radius of the capsule.  
- get_radius() → float: Returns the current radius.  
- set_length(value: float) → void: Sets the length of the capsule.  
- get_length() → float: Returns the current length.  

Note: Collision layers and masks use bitwise operations to define interactions between objects.  
Warning: Modifying properties at runtime may affect physics simulation stability.  
Tip: Use with CollisionShape2D nodes for active collision detection in scenes.
